From: Theodore Ts'o <tytso@mit.edu>
Date: Tue, 6 Nov 2018 17:18:17 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] ext4: avoid possible double brelse() in add_new_gdb() on
 error path
References: bnc#1012382
Patch-mainline: 4.4.164
Git-commit: 4f32c38b4662312dd3c5f113d8bdd459887fb773

commit 4f32c38b4662312dd3c5f113d8bdd459887fb773 upstream.

Fixes: b40971426a83 ("ext4: add error checking to calls to ...")
Reported-by: Vasily Averin <vvs@virtuozzo.com>
Signed-off-by: Theodore Ts'o <tytso@mit.edu>
Cc: stable@kernel.org # 2.6.38
Signed-off-by: Greg Kroah-Hartman <gregkh@linuxfoundation.org>
Signed-off-by: Jiri Slaby <jslaby@suse.cz>
---
 fs/ext4/resize.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/fs/ext4/resize.c b/fs/ext4/resize.c
index 82df738e5403..bad13f049fb0 100644
--- a/fs/ext4/resize.c
+++ b/fs/ext4/resize.c
@@ -844,6 +844,7 @@ static int add_new_gdb(handle_t *handle, struct inode *inode,
 	err = ext4_handle_dirty_metadata(handle, NULL, gdb_bh);
 	if (unlikely(err)) {
 		ext4_std_error(sb, err);
+		iloc.bh = NULL;
 		goto exit_inode;
 	}
 	brelse(dind);
